===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
[[Image:Amerigo vespucci 1976 nyc aufgetakelt.jpg|thumb|A '''ship''' (sense 1).]]

# A large, [[water]]-[[borne]] [[vessel]], in contrast to a [[boat]].
# {{especially|in combination}} A vessel which travels through any medium other than across land, such as an [[airship]] or [[spaceship]].

====Usage notes====
* The singular form {{term||ship}} is often used without any [[Appendix:Glossary#article|article]], producing such sentences as "In all, we spent three weeks aboard ship." and "Abandon ship!". (Similar patterns may be seen with many place nouns, such as {{term|camp}}, {{term|home}}, {{term|work}}, and {{term|school}}, but the details vary from noun to noun.)

